main event: The observer witnessed several unidentified flying objects (UFOs) over a period of time near Washington, D.C. on August 8, 1966.
interesting points: The observer saw four bright, circular yellowish objects, about 30 to 60 feet in diameter, moving silently from north to south at an altitude of around 2,000 feet.
Later, the observer saw two similar objects pass overhead from east to west at an estimated altitude of 40,000 feet, appearing to flutter and glitter as they moved.
The observer also saw a small, greyish-white object, approximately 3-4 feet in diameter, drifting down at a 45-degree angle behind some trees.
The observer was able to continuously observe the objects for over a mile while driving along the highway.
The observer was asked secretly by the base commander about the sighting.
sighted object: multiple unidentified flying objects, including bright circular objects and a smaller drifting object
photographs: no, the report does not mention any photographs
